uaries. The Family Is Alive. New York, Tel Aviv, Ma’agan Michael -- tAppendix -- tNotes -- tThe Family Tree -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Kahans from Baku is a saga of a Russian Jewish family. Their story also provides an insight into the history of Jews in the Imperial Russian economy, especially in the oil industry. The entrepreneur and family patriarch, Chaim Kahan was a pious and enlightened man and a Zionist. His children followed in his footsteps in business as well as in policy, philanthropy and love of books. The Kahans from Baku takes us through a forced migration history in times of war and revolution and the 20th century’s totalitarian regimes telling a story of fortune and misfortune in economy and everyday life of one cohesive family over four generations in Russia, Germany, Denmark and France, ending up in Palestine and the United States of America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJewish businesspeoplezEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish businesspeoplezGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 0aJewish businesspeoplezGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish businesspeoplezRussia (Federation)xHistoryy19th century. 0aJewish businesspeoplezRussia (Federation)xHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszAzerbaijanzBaku. 0aJewszRussia (Federation)xHistoryy19th century. 0aJewszRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexHistoryy19th century. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexHistoryy20 century. 0aZionismzEuropexHistoryy19th century. 0aZionismzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aAzerbaijan.  aForced migration.  aModern Jewish history.  aNazi Germany.  aRussian Revolution.  aZionist movement.  adiaspora.  afamily.  aoil industry.  apu